<p><a name="Blackman_windows" id="Blackman_windows"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Window_function&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Blackman windows">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Blackman windows</span></h4>
<p>Blackman windows are defined as:<sup id="cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-K-term_windows-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="w(n)=a_0 - a_1 \cos \left ( \frac{2 \pi n}{N-1} \right) + a_2 \cos \left ( \frac{4 \pi n}{N-1} \right)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/e/b/d/ebd51837180dfda43f57b257f9743489.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="a_0=\frac{1-\alpha}{2};\quad a_1=\frac{1}{2};\quad a_2=\frac{\alpha}{2}\," src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/8/4/4841cc099ebcbad8aa27a3dcbd4b899b.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>By common convention, the unqualified term <i>Blackman window</i> refers to α=0.16.</p>
<div style="clear:both"></div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Window_function_(Kaiser;_alpha_%3D_2_pi).png" class="image" title="Kaiser window, α =2π; B=1.5"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Window_function_%28Kaiser%3B_alpha_%3D_2_pi%29.png/180px-Window_function_%28Kaiser%3B_alpha_%3D_2_pi%29.png" width="180" height="61" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Window_function_(Kaiser;_alpha_%3D_2_pi).png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Kaiser window, α =2π; B=1.5</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Window_function_(Kaiser;_alpha_%3D_3_pi).png" class="image" title="Kaiser window, α =3π; B=1.8"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Window_function_%28Kaiser%3B_alpha_%3D_3_pi%29.png/180px-Window_function_%28Kaiser%3B_alpha_%3D_3_pi%29.png" width="180" height="61" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Window_function_(Kaiser;_alpha_%3D_3_pi).png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Kaiser window, α =3π; B=1.8</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Kaiser_windows" id="Kaiser_windows"></a></p>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Window_function&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Kaiser windows">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Kaiser windows</span></h4>
<div class="rellink noprint relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Kaiser_window" title="Kaiser window">Kaiser window</a></div>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="w(n)=\frac{I_0\Bigg (\alpha \sqrt{1 - (\begin{matrix} \frac{2 n}{N-1} \end{matrix}-1)^2}\Bigg )} {I_0(\alpha)}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/5/1/851ad57e87175284d8d6eeec35472578.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li>Note that:</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="
w_0(n) = \frac{I_0\Bigg (\alpha \sqrt{1 - (\begin{matrix} \frac{2 n}{N-1} \end{matrix})^2}\Bigg )} {I_0(\alpha)}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/9/b/79b7855e124b97e3d130c90e28a46562.png" /></dd>
</dl>
