<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCarlo_Cattani_and_Jeremiah_Rushchitsky2007">Carlo Cattani and Jeremiah Rushchitsky (2007). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=JuJKu_0KDycC&amp;pg=PA53&amp;dq=define+%22window+function%22+nonzero+interval&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=3&amp;ei=iyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ&amp;sig=ACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg#PPA53,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=JuJKu_0KDycC&amp;pg=PA53&amp;dq=define+%22window+function%22+nonzero+interval&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=3&amp;ei=iyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ&amp;sig=ACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg#PPA53,M1" rel="nofollow">Wavelet and Wave Analysis As Applied to Materials With Micro Or Nanostructure</a></i>. World Scientific. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9812707840" class="internal">ISBN 9812707840</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=JuJKu_0KDycC&amp;pg=PA53&amp;dq=define+%22window+function%22+nonzero+interval&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=3&amp;ei=iyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ&amp;sig=ACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg#PPA53,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=JuJKu_0KDycC&amp;pg=PA53&amp;dq=define+%22window+function%22+nonzero+interval&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=3&amp;ei=iyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ&amp;sig=ACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg#PPA53,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=JuJKu_0KDycC&amp;pg=PA53&amp;dq=define+%22window+function%22+nonzero+interval&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=3&amp;ei=iyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ&amp;sig=ACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg#PPA53,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Wavelet+and+Wave+Analysis+As+Applied+to+Materials+With+Micro+Or+Nanostructure&amp;rft.aulast=Carlo+Cattani+and+Jeremiah+Rushchitsky&amp;rft.au=Carlo+Cattani+and+Jeremiah+Rushchitsky&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pub=World+Scientific&amp;rft.isbn=9812707840&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DJuJKu_0KDycC%26pg%3DPA53%26dq%3Ddefine%2B%2522window%2Bfunction%2522%2Bnonzero%2Binterval%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D3%26ei%3DiyGbSKX_OJCKtAPXwaD2CQ%26sig%3DACfU3U1zZzq20w9GO1fbmNcvD3MlQFevsg%23PPA53%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCurtis_Roads2002">Curtis Roads (2002). <i>Microsound</i>. MIT Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0262182157" class="internal">ISBN 0262182157</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Microsound&amp;rft.aulast=Curtis+Roads&amp;rft.au=Curtis+Roads&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=MIT+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0262182157&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.cg.tuwien.ac.at/research/vis/vismed/Windows/MasteringWindows.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.cg.tuwien.ac.at/research/vis/vismed/Windows/MasteringWindows.pdf" rel="nofollow">Mastering Windows: Improving Reconstruction</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-K-term_windows-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-6" title=""><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-K-term_windows_4-7" title=""><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> Windows of the form<b>:</b>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="w(n)=\sum_{k=0}^{K} a_k \cos \left(\frac{2\pi k n}{N-1}\right)" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/f/2/6f2028e8dba17291853c186f423833b1.png" /></dd>
</dl>
have only 2K+1 non-zero DFT coefficients, which makes them good choices for applications that require <a href="/wiki/Discrete_Fourier_transform#Convolution_theorem_duality" title="Discrete Fourier transform">windowing by convolution in the frequency-domain</a>. In those applications, the DFT of the <u>unwindowed</u> data vector is needed for a different purpose than spectral analysis. (see <a href="/wiki/Overlap-save_method#Extending_Overlap-Save" title="Overlap-save method">Overlap-save method</a>)</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFLoren_D._Enochson_and_Robert_K._Otnes1968">Loren D. Enochson and Robert K. Otnes (1968). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=duBQAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;dq=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;ei=4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA&amp;pgis=1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=duBQAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;dq=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;ei=4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA&amp;pgis=1" rel="nofollow">Programming and Analysis for Digital Time Series Data</a></i>. U.S. Dept. of Defense, Shock and Vibration Info. Center. pp.&#160;142<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=duBQAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;dq=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;ei=4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA&amp;pgis=1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=duBQAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;dq=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;ei=4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA&amp;pgis=1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=duBQAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;dq=%22hamming+window%22+date:0-1970&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;ei=4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA&amp;pgis=1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Programming+and+Analysis+for+Digital+Time+Series+Data&amp;rft.aulast=Loren+D.+Enochson+and+Robert+K.+Otnes&amp;rft.au=Loren+D.+Enochson+and+Robert+K.+Otnes&amp;rft.date=1968&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B142&amp;rft.pub=U.S.+Dept.+of+Defense%2C+Shock+and+Vibration+Info.+Center&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DduBQAAAAMAAJ%26q%3D%2522hamming%2Bwindow%2522%2Bdate%3A0-1970%26dq%3D%2522hamming%2Bwindow%2522%2Bdate%3A0-1970%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%26ei%3D4LEASfHtJoXWsgOcz7WdDA%26pgis%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="Other_references" id="Other_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Window_function&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: Other references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Other references</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFharris1978">harris, fredric j. (January 1978). "<a href="http://web.mit.edu/xiphmont/Public/windows.pdf" class="external text" title="http://web.mit.edu/xiphmont/Public/windows.pdf" rel="nofollow">"On the use of Windows for Harmonic Analysis with the Discrete Fourier Transform"</a>". <i>Proceedings of the IEEE</i> <b>66</b> (1): 51–83.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fweb.mit.edu%2Fxiphmont%2FPublic%2Fwindows.pdf+%22On+the+use+of+Windows+for+Harmonic+Analysis+with+the+Discrete+Fourier+Transform%22%5D&amp;rft.jtitle=Proceedings+of+the+IEEE&amp;rft.aulast=harris&amp;rft.aufirst=fredric+j.&amp;rft.au=harris%2C+fredric+j.&amp;rft.date=January+1978&amp;rft.volume=66&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=51%E2%80%9383&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Article on FFT windows which introduced many of the key metrics used to compare windows.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFNuttall1981">Nuttall, Albert H. (February 1981). "Some Windows with Very Good Sidelobe Behavior". <i>IEEE Transactions on Acoustics, Speech, and Signal Processing</i> <b>29</b> (1): 84-91.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Some+Windows+with+Very+Good+Sidelobe+Behavior&amp;rft.jtitle=IEEE+Transactions+on+Acoustics%2C+Speech%2C+and+Signal+Processing&amp;rft.aulast=Nuttall&amp;rft.aufirst=Albert+H.&amp;rft.au=Nuttall%2C+Albert+H.&amp;rft.date=February+1981&amp;rft.volume=29&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=84-91&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Extends Harris' paper, covering all the window functions known at the time, along with key metric comparisons.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFOppenheim.2C_Alan_V..3B_Schafer.2C_Ronald_W..3B_Buck.2C_John_A.1999">Oppenheim, Alan V.; Schafer, Ronald W.; Buck, John A. (1999). <i>Discrete-time signal processing</i>. Upper Saddle River, N.J.: Prentice Hall. pp.&#160;468–471. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0137549202" class="internal">ISBN 0-13-754920-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Discrete-time+signal+processing&amp;rft.aulast=Oppenheim%2C+Alan+V.%3B+Schafer%2C+Ronald+W.%3B+Buck%2C+John+A.&amp;rft.au=Oppenheim%2C+Alan+V.%3B+Schafer%2C+Ronald+W.%3B+Buck%2C+John+A.&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B468%E2%80%93471&amp;rft.place=Upper+Saddle+River%2C+N.J.&amp;rft.pub=Prentice+Hall&amp;rft.isbn=0-13-754920-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBergenA._Antoniou2009">Bergen, S.W.A.; A. Antoniou (2004). "Design of Ultraspherical Window Functions with Prescribed Spectral Characteristics". <i>EURASIP Journal on Applied Signal Processing</i> <b>2004</b> (13): 2053–2065. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1155%2FS1110865704403114" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1155%2FS1110865704403114" rel="nofollow">10.1155/S1110865704403114</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Design+of+Ultraspherical+Window+Functions+with+Prescribed+Spectral+Characteristics&amp;rft.jtitle=EURASIP+Journal+on+Applied+Signal+Processing&amp;rft.aulast=Bergen&amp;rft.aufirst=S.W.A.&amp;rft.au=Bergen%2C+S.W.A.&amp;rft.au=A.+Antoniou&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=2004&amp;rft.issue=13&amp;rft.pages=2053%E2%80%932065&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1155%2FS1110865704403114&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBergenA._Antoniou2009">Bergen, S.W.A.; A. Antoniou (2005). "Design of Nonrecursive Digital Filters Using the Ultraspherical Window Function". <i>EURASIP Journal on Applied Signal Processing</i> <b>2005</b> (12): 1910–1922. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1155%2FASP.2005.1910" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1155%2FASP.2005.1910" rel="nofollow">10.1155/ASP.2005.1910</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Design+of+Nonrecursive+Digital+Filters+Using+the+Ultraspherical+Window+Function&amp;rft.jtitle=EURASIP+Journal+on+Applied+Signal+Processing&amp;rft.aulast=Bergen&amp;rft.aufirst=S.W.A.&amp;rft.au=Bergen%2C+S.W.A.&amp;rft.au=A.+Antoniou&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=2005&amp;rft.issue=12&amp;rft.pages=1910%E2%80%931922&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1155%2FASP.2005.1910&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Window_function"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
